				<div class="post-heading">
					<h1>Troubleshooting your Furby</h1>
					<span class="heading-author">Eric</span> 
					<span class="heading-date">December 26, 2012</span>
					<span class="heading-comments"><a href="http://www.furbymanual.com/troubleshooting-your-furby/#comments" title="Comment on Troubleshooting your Furby">288</a></span>
				</div>
				
								
								
												
				<div class="post-entry">
										
					<p><!-- AdSense Now! V4.33 --><br />
<!-- Post[leadin] --></p>
<div class="adsense adsense-leadin" style="text-align:center;margin: 12px;"><script type="text/javascript"><!--
google_ad_client = "ca-pub-1470353520081367";
/* FurbyManualMain */
google_ad_slot = "5106505393";
google_ad_width = 468;
google_ad_height = 15;
//-->
</script><br />
<script type="text/javascript"
src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">
</script></div>
<p><!-- AdSense Now! V4.33 --><br />
<span style="font-size: large;">How do I reset my Furby?!?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: large;">I&#8217;m hearing from a lot of people that some of the new Furbies have a case of narcolepsy (aka they wont stay awake).   Rather than have everyone read through ideas in the comments of other posts, I want to list everything here in one post for you.   Hopefully some of you will get your little critters running again!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: large;"> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: large;">Your Furby keeps going to sleep.  Your Furby&#8217;s eyes light up but he does not respond.  Your Furby makes a buzzing noise.  Your Furby seems to be DOA and wont come on at all.  There are several scenarios and unfortunately only a few possibilities.  Lets go over them:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: large;"> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: large;">1.  Make sure good, fresh batteries are installed and that they are all installed correctly (all pointing the right directions as illustrated in the battery compartment)</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: large;">2.  Remove the base of your Furby and push the “refresh button” for 2 seconds, then replace the base. This will reset the hardware while retaining all of Furby’s personality.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<div class="video-shortcode"><iframe title="YouTube video player" width="600" height="350" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ix8SkMe7PCs" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>
</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: large;">3. If step two does not work, you may want to return or exchange your Furby where you purchased it (you can do this even if you bought it on eBay).</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: large;">4. Last ditch effort, call Hasbro Customer service at: 1-800-327-8264 or in the UK the number is: 00800 22 42 72 76</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Step two is said to work most of the time, hopefully it will work for you!</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.furbymanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/furby-reset-button.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-267 aligncenter" alt="Image Courtesy of Hasbro" src="http://www.furbymanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/furby-reset-button-300x201.png" width="300" height="201" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;<!-- AdSense Now! V4.33 --><br />
<!-- Post[leadout] --></p>
