				<div class="comment-text">
					
					<p>I understand your frustration Jamie (believe me I do!), that&#8217;s why I set up this site.  I&#8217;ve always thought Furbies are neat toys and just wanted to help people with the sleeping/dying Furby problems and share ideas with others who have purchased them. Please keep in mind that Hasbro does not own or operate this site, its just me sharing the few fixes that exist.  There are actually thousands of people who have Furbies and never experienced any problems, then there are those of us who have picked up a faulty one (including myself once).  I&#8217;m not sure why there are so many malfunctioning Furbies but don&#8217;t lose hope, Hasbro has been very good about exchanging them (including the shipping).  It is a pain that no one should have go through, but at least they are willing to cooperate by sending out a new one.</p>

