<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-1206">
	
		<div class="the-comment">
		
			<img alt='Eric' src='http://www.furbymanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/furby_510x317-60x60.jpg' class='avatar avatar-60 photo' height='60' width='60' />
			
			<div class="comment-arrow"></div>
			
			<div class="comment-box">
			
				<div class="comment-author">
					<strong>admin</strong>
					<small>December 29, 2013 at 4:23 am</a> - <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/troubleshooting-your-furby/?replytocom=1206#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("-1206", "1206", "respond", "167")'>Reply</a></small>
				</div>
			
				<div class="comment-text">
					
					<p>Rechargeable batteries shouldn&#8217;t harm your Furby, but they don&#8217;t last as long or perform as well as the regular &#8220;Throw-away&#8221; type batteries.  They don&#8217;t always hold a full charge and may not be strong enough for your Furby to always perform its best.</p>

				</div>
			
			</div>
			
		</div>

