	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-1439">
	
		<div class="the-comment">
		
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/4004763d80da3a104dba0e1bd051f5fc?s=60&amp;d=wavatar&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-60 photo' height='60' width='60' />
			
			<div class="comment-arrow"></div>
			
			<div class="comment-box">
			
				<div class="comment-author">
					<strong>Larry B</strong>
					<small>January 13, 2014 at 4:05 am</a> - <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/troubleshooting-your-furby/?replytocom=1439#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("-1439", "1439", "respond", "167")'>Reply</a></small>
				</div>
			
				<div class="comment-text">
					
					<p>Furby Boom stop moving but still has lights and sound? It&#8217;s the wires on the motor. This is not the same issue the last Furby had with the motor getting stuck but an all new problem with the Furby Boom.<br />
 I have worked on 2 of them and both had the same problem the brown wire was broke loose from the motor. Re-attach the wire use a lighter to melt down the shrink tape and your good to go.<br />
 I will say it&#8217;s a pain in the backside to get the Boom model apart.</p>

				</div>
			
			</div>
			
		</div>

